OL,17,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,18,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779152631
OL,3,CAndy Burnham returns: I will take my
OL,4,Cfight 'as high as I can go'
OL,6,FOver the course of the interview,
OL,7,FBurnham elaborated on how he feels the
OL,8,FLabour government, under Sir Keir
OL,9,FStarmer, has failed to change the
OL,10,Fcountry in the ways he thinks are
OL,11,Fneeded. He sees Britain's current
OL,12,Fcourse as one of decline.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779152631
OL,3,CAndy Burnham returns: I will take my
OL,4,Cfight 'as high as I can go'
OL,6,F"I think Britain started on a path in
OL,7,Fthe mid-1980s that is the path that
OL,8,Fhas led us to where we are today. It
OL,9,Fstarted with de-industrialisation in
OL,10,Fthese parts. I was growing up here,
OL,11,Fthe miners strike, this was a mining
OL,12,Farea and that was devastating. As well
OL,13,Fas the loss of other industry, de-
OL,14,Findustrialisation, deregulation.
OL,16,F"For me we need a different path that
OL,17,Fputs those things back under public
OL,18,Fcontrol, makes them more affordable.
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31217
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779152631
OL,3,CAndy Burnham returns: I will take my
OL,4,Cfight 'as high as I can go'
OL,6,F"The path that Britain has been on for
OL,7,F40 years, in my view, has been the
OL,8,Fwrong path. It's taken us to this
OL,9,Fplace where people can't afford life's
OL,10,Fbasics, they can't afford a few pints
OL,11,Fat the weekend, they can't afford a
OL,12,Fholiday. And that's why they're saying
OL,13,Fto politicians, do better. This is not
OL,14,Fgood enough. And they're right to say
OL,15,Fthat. I'm saying there's a new path
OL,16,Fhere, new politics to build a new
OL,17,Feconomy for Britain."
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31218
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779152631
OL,3,CAndy Burnham returns: I will take my
OL,4,Cfight 'as high as I can go'
OL,6,F"That is the main question in this by-
OL,7,Felection. Are people happy to stick on
OL,8,Fthe path that Britain's been on for 40
OL,9,Fyears or do we want new path?"
OL,11,FHe has previously signalled he would
OL,12,Fsupport Britain rejoining the EU. He
OL,13,Fsaid it was not a focus for this by-
OL,14,Felection ` but didn't completely shy
OL,15,Faway from what he called a longer term
OL,16,Fcase.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31219
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779152631
OL,3,CAndy Burnham returns: I will take my
OL,4,Cfight 'as high as I can go'
OL,6,F"In the long-term there is a case for
OL,7,Fthat, but I'm not advocating that in
OL,8,Fthis by-election. In fact, what I am
OL,9,Fsaying is focus now domestically.
OL,10,FBritain has got to focus very much on
OL,11,Fthe here and now and the issues that
OL,12,Fare affecting people."
OL,14,FBurnham has faced tough questions
OL,15,Fabout what his potential policy
OL,16,Fplatform of increased public ownership
OL,17,Fcould mean for market stability.
